column3: "I played the game out to completion, making o's completely defensive and there is a definite solution "
"I looked at the best location to place my first X and then worked it out from there by trail and error."
"I just went through all kinds of moves to find one that I know x would win first."

"I marked the spot on the board that would leave two possible ways to win open. Then for my second move I placed the marker where it needed to be to setup a guaranteed win. Once I placed that marker I had to ways to win and then I won."
"I used that strategy as an defensive move to block o from being able to place any strategic moves/win. "
"Forces him to constantly block you, until you win"
"Trying to force \"O\" to react to me defensively rather than having the time to make offensive moves."
"I tried to think about where I could place X and where O would go to counter it."
"To make O think of a different strategy and not notice the angle which I am considering."
"trying to find the best optimal way and seeing how many options x has."
"I had to guess because I could not figure it out no matter how hard I tried. "
"i made each move to force 'O' into a situation where they needed to block the tic-tac-toe.. So i put 'O' into check each turn making the solution easier to find."
"I looked at how I could prevent O from blocking me. "
"I tried to think about where the next player would try to block me and be as strategic as possible."
"Just trial, error, and simulation. I don't know enough math to do anything else."
"I was trying to learn the game and make the moves to make sure X won"
"I tried many different approaches, but always ended up with O winning.  I don't think I figured it out."

"As the X player I tried to make a move each time that would force the O player to make a specific move that would prevent me from winning the next turn. My main focus was to line up three squares with an X either horizontally, vertically, or diagonally to control the flow of the game."
"I just think about the best strategy. "
"I went with the area I would have the most room to work with rather than be constricted."
"Tried to maximize how many angles I could get 4 in a row while blocking the opponent at 3. "
"Forcing O to make moves that allow me to make moves that have multiple next moves"
"I looked for any move that forced the opponent to make a play.  That allowed me to create a series of 3 Xs that had no Os at either end."
"I tried solutions that were defensive, disallowing the opponent to get me trapped, and I saw the eventual solution present itself"
"I thought he doesn't have a lot of choices because he is threatened"
"I kept resetting the board until I could line up 4 X's."
"I tried to put my moves in a place that would force the other player to have to block me so they could not go on offense"
"Used the boxes to see what possible moves were available"
"used quickest way for x to achieve 4 in a row"
"I tried to experiment using that cell and work through several solutions."
"I went through and tried to always back 0 into a corner whereby eventually they would be forced in a situation where I had two places to win heading into their turn."
"I just tried many different scenarios until I found one that made the most sense"

"I just played it out. I put the first move for X in an area that was centrally located, so that there were a lot of options for X to go next. As I played it out, O was simply unable to block all the areas that were possible for X."
"I tried to find a way to give x 2 options for where to place the last one to win, so that o could not block them both."
"I tried to think ahead and also think what o would do"
"I imagined the places that O would try to win and made sure to block those while leaving several openings for X"
"I thought through potential moves and also the other players possible moves and chose what I felt was my best chance of winning."
"i made sure that o couldn't score first"

"I just played the game and tried as best as I could to think multiple moves ahead to get X into the guaranteed winnable situation. If I found what I thought would be a winning scenario then I would go back and think about how O might play differently to defeat it."
"I noticed that unless I forced o to make a certain move he would win in two turns, so I kept forcing o untill I was in a position to gain three in a row with no end caps"
"I chose the box that I felt ensured gave me the best chance based on predicted counter moves by O."
"every next move should open 3 new options for a win, by the 4th move you will only need to place the X where you have 2 options to win in the next move to not be blocked, like chess"
